Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of an open-source unsupervised approach to Named Entity Recognition and Linking (NER+L) in biomedical documents such as Electronic Health Records (EHRs). This involves the use of machine learning to extract and structure information from unstructured text. The paper also discusses the validation of the approach on biomedical databases and papers. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CY (Computers and Society), which all have relevance to the development and application of machine learning techniques in the biomedical domain.
